<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12217g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12217g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12217g"> 217(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> canonized bones &becaus; / found in catacombs</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On glorifie parfois ceux qui sont morts en un lieu saint, ou bien encore ceux dont on y a d&eacute;couvert les reliques. C&apos;est le cas de nombreux saints chr&eacute;tiens qui doivent leur inscription au martyrologe au seul fait que leurs ossements ont &eacute;t&eacute; d&eacute;couverts dans les catacombes <br><font color="green">[One often glorifies those who have died in a sacred place, or even those whose relics have been found in such places. This is the case with quite a few Christian saints who owe their inclusion in the martyrology to the single fact that their bones were found in the catacombs]</font> <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) 26</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
